items.text: One of the best chicken rice in Singapore. The meat is so good. Brush up on your mandarin when ordering (singlish also can lah)

Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice There is always a line outside this popular stand at Maxwell Road, but it’s worth the wait.
dirt cheap chicken rice, very tasty and coincindentally one that antony bordain boasts about
the line for ordering and paying are different, make sure you stand in the right line http://food.juicyjelly.net/2014/01/bites-tian-tian-hainanese-chicken.html
The best!! Worth waiting in a long line. Ask for extra sauce.
Not a major chicken rice fan but this one has my vote. Is yummy and will queue for it.
絶品チキンライス！一皿3.5ドルだけど、人数多いならご飯とチキン（whole/half）を別々に頼むとたくさんチキン食べられるよ。
Mediocre. White meat? No real flavor. Good chili paste.
As featured by Anthony Bourdain, the hainanese chicken rice is great. Is there better? Probably. Is there cheaper? Yes. But is there anything bad about this one? No.
Line of 10 people at 455pm
初めて来たら食べるべし。何度も食べる必要なし。他のもの食べようよ！
Obviously go for the chicken rice, but be prepared for a wait.  The market its in is also not the cleanest.
Of course chicken rice one of the best in Singapore lah!! Come early, 10.30 am to avoid the long queue. I only queue 3 people in front of me.
This is IMO the best chicken rice you can find in Singapore. The chicken is very tender (and juicy) coupled with tasty sauce. Their rice is a BOMB....very fragrant. Side dishes are also good.
雞肉真的很嫩！老闆娘親自出菜
Queue's always long so you need to be extra patient – food's great & definitely worth the wait.
The birthplace of Chicken Rice in SG. It's worth the wait.Ü
Extremely good chicken rice costing S$5. Sometimes queues gets quite big, but they serve people very fast so that isn't a problem.
They now have a second branch at Joo Chiat - less queues, aircon and other dishes in a nice clean yet cosy setting
Nice tender chicken, worth the wait. The crowd moves fast, waiting time was circa 20 mins.
Chicken rice ลือชื่อ!!
Chicken rice: Chicken is steamed or boiled until it is just cooked & still a little bit pink near the bone. It's served with oily rice that's made with chicken broth & slices of cucumber on the side.
The queues here are unbelievably long! But the hainanese chicken rice was quite good though.
薄味で炊いたライス、柔らかく臭みがないチキン。嬉しい味のバランス❗️日本米で食べたいもんだ。
Chicken was tender, the best part was the rice
Arrive before 11:30. Ask for breast meat and off the bone if you hate bones like me. And ask for dark soy sauce on the side!
Best chili saucee
The Hainanese Chicken rice is so great that you need to take twice!

Really good chicken rice, the chicken meat is juicy, the rice is fragrance, the gravy source is flavorful with chicken stock, the dipping is full with garlic and chilli. A combination of good things!!
Looks good hahahaha queue is long but they process the order fast so its ok :)
Just follow the queue and can't be wrong ! First queue to pay and second one to collect the chicken rice.
Cue moves quickly
No other stall has a queue. Bourdain has done it. Perhaps indication it is one the best? I enjoyed medium sized Hainan chicken rice ;)
Anthony Bourdain, clearly you need more time in Singapore because this chicken rice is good but not wow as you said..
The best joint inside Maxwell! Half a chicken will be enough grub for 2-3 people!
Overrated. Most of the stalls in the city can make the chicken. It is the rice and the black sauce make the difference. Tho I like the thickness of the sauce but found both rice and the sauce bland.
Chicken is yummy
Standard dropped till it is no better than e average neighbourhood chicken rice stalls.Not worth eating again. Strike off my list.
Recommended! Best hainanese chicken rice i've ever eat in Singapore! 👍
Famous chicken rice, chilli sauce includes lime, but the chicken is the star, gelatinous skin. Yum.
Chicken rice dip chilly sauce!
Anthony Bourdain's effect
In my top 5 chicken rice in singapore list. Plus Anthony Bourdain says it's awesome too.
Honestly probably my least favorite of the 3-4 chicken rices I've tried in Singapore (the others were random walk ins)
best chicken rice
The chicken is awesome!!!!
There is a restaurant (with air-con) set up at Joo Chiat (next to Joo Chiat CC). Check it out!
top 10 street foods
dark soy sauce is not sweet one.. be careful!!
Visited on 29 March 15. Had an unexpected experience.

One of the best chicken rice in Singapore!
This is a good Chicken rice! The size is small!
Chicken is cold, rice is dry, chilli is tasteless, how did this get voted as a top stall?
Chicken rice just about lived up to its lofty rep

$5 for a plate of chicken rice. Flavoursome rice-make sure you taste it first unadulterated. Chicken is tender n succulent. Sauce is spicy, perhaps a bit overwhelming,takes away from that awesome rice
Chicken 🍚
Roasted chicken and rice
Good meal.
The hype is mildly justified. Lines get long during peak hours (12pm and 6pm). If possible, come during tea time (3-4pm).
Succulent strips of chicken with fragrant rice. Really tasty.
It opens at 11am should arrive early otherwise u have to wait long line but it's worth waiting!
Overrated. Eat here if you just want to brag that you ate the same chicken rice as Anthony Bourdain.
Long queue but worth to try it. The Chili sauce is spicy not recommend for those who can't take spicy
Anthony Bourdain would so take back hid words if he gets to taste their rice now - dry n clumpy! Chicken n chllii sauce r good tough :)
One of the best chicken rice stalls in Singapore. If you want the real deal, this is the one.
A national dish and where better than at Tian Tian Chicken Rice. It’s open-air, non-air condtioned, so be prepared.
Nice plate of chicken. The place is very crowded but the line is really fast. Is good but nothing to die for, I had better meals on the other Chinatown complex food center.
White chicken: 4.5/5 [chicken meat a bit stringy]Chicken rice: 4.25/5Chilli sauce: 4.5/5Ginger sauce: average.
Of course the chicken rice lah.. 😄 and the gizzard. One of the best indeed..
Awful and overrated
Pay first on the right hand stall & collect on the left. Least crowded time for dinner is 6pm.
Long queues but fast-moving. The chicken rice is good, but nothing exceptional.
This place was worth the wait. Amazing chicken rice.
Best chicken rice! Order half or whole chicken to share is more cost effective.
Came just for the rice...I wonder if it was AB first encounter with CR ...will stay with my food court CR, ... anytime. Chilli sauce is good though.
Too oily

Sold out！so sad
The meat is very tender!
Homely chicken rice, not the most flavourful, but it's homely.
Rice really is that good. Can ask them to go easy on the sauce.
order a half chicken rice and ask for more sauce on top! perfectly cooked chicken!
Chicken rice 👍🏻🕴.  Featured on Anthony Bourdain I believe

Chicken was mostly bone. Rice wasn't even that good. Don't bother.
さすが有名店。激しく美味い(*´艸｀*)
Line moves quickly. Get the chicken and rice. Classic.
chicken rice + two chili sauce = i'm gooddd (kanye voice)
Best chicken rice ever!

...Her favourite is served at Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice, in the Maxwell Food Centre. “But go early,” Pamela adds. “Sometimes you have to wait for two hours.”...
Long queue, but quite fast! Chicken OK, rice no good.
Best chicken rice in Singapore? Really?
Best chicken riceeeeee
This is the best Chicken Rice in Singapore :)
One of the best places for chicken rice in Singapore and this stall's version has beaten Gordon Ramsay's version of chicken rice in the SingTel Hawker Heroes contest.
nice chicken rice ridiculous queue
